The paper discusses the use of nuclear norm minimization in machine learning and computer vision, which are both subfields of CS. The problem being addressed, Low-Rank Representation (LRR), is commonly used in these subfields. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are all likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to prove a lemma, which suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
